490eaa7a-3136-4e3f-bbbd-72e7ead9b5b2.15ca4e6a-c29c-49d1-aed5-07ecb330f595.description=This subflow queries the InfraDB to select the CCNAME from Cloudcell based on the datacell acronym. inpput\: server.1.datacenter The acronym in the datacenter table 490eaa7a-3136-4e3f-bbbd-72e7ead9b5b2.31f0fe2c-f3c8-4c8d-847c-ce154d023cf4.transition.description=SLA2 490eaa7a-3136-4e3f-bbbd-72e7ead9b5b2.53e97188-f397-44b1-b71f-573bf7d2e5fd.description=
This operation checks whether a string matches another string, using a specific matching rule. The "toMatch" input is the string that is checked for matching the "matchTo" expression. 

Inputs\:
    matchType - The type of match to perform.
Valid values\: Exact Match, Contains, Contains Once, Does Not Contain, Match All Words, Match No Words, Regex
Default value\: Exact Match
    toMatch - The string that is checked for matching.
    matchTo - The string to match against.
Example\: If "matchType" is “RegEx”, the "matchTo" input is a regular expression such as\: ^-?\d+(([\.,]\d+)?)+$. 
    ignoreCase - Specifies whether to ignore case when matching or not.
Valid values\: False, True
Default value\: False

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the string "Matches" if the "toMatch" string matches the "matchTo" string. Otherwise, it contains the string "Does Not Match".  

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.
490eaa7a-3136-4e3f-bbbd-72e7ead9b5b2.8e6d82fe-21d3-4b76-b722-755689cb2679.description=
This operation is used to retrieve a value from a list. When the index of an element from a list is known, this operation can be used to extract the element.

Inputs\:
    list - A list to get the value from.
    delimiter - The delimiter that separates values in the list.
Default value\: ','
    index - The index of the value (starting at 0) to retrieve from the list.
Valid values\: an integer, end (for the last element), end-1 (for the second to last element)

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the value found at the specified index in the list, if the value specified for the "index" input field is positive and less than the size of the list. Otherwise, it contains the value specified for "index".

Responses\:
     success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
     failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.
